{"parse":{"title":"Heed Their Rising Voices","pageid":39133027,"revid":770222492,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Heed_Their_Rising_Voices.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Heed_Their_Rising_Voices.jpg/220px-Heed_Their_Rising_Voices.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"338\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Heed_Their_Rising_Voices.jpg/330px-Heed_Their_Rising_Voices.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Heed_Their_Rising_Voices.jpg/440px-Heed_Their_Rising_Voices.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1025\" data-file-height=\"1574\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Heed_Their_Rising_Voices.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Published in <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Times\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York Times\">New York Times</a></i> on March 29, 1960</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Heed Their Rising Voices</b> is a 1960 newspaper advertisement published in the <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Times\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York Times\">New York Times</a></i>.  It was published on March 29, 1960 and paid for by the \"Committee to Defend Martin Luther King and the Struggle for Freedom in the South\".  The purpose of the advertisement was to draw attention and support towards <a href=\"/wiki/Martin_Luther_King_Jr.\" title=\"Martin Luther King Jr.\">Martin Luther King Jr.</a> A recent felony charge of perjury was leveled against him and could have resulted in a lengthy imprisonment.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  The headline of the advertisement was drawn from a phrase used in the <i>New York Times</i> editorial, \"Amendment XV\", published on March 19, 1960.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Hall_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Hall-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>  The advertisement became the source of a <a href=\"/wiki/Defamation\" title=\"Defamation\">libel suit</a> in the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Supreme_Court\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"United States Supreme Court\">United States Supreme Court</a> case <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Times_Co._v._Sullivan\" title=\"New York Times Co. v. Sullivan\">New York Times Co. v. Sullivan</a></i> (1964).<sup id=\"cite_ref-Hall_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Hall-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Heed_Their_Rising_Voices&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Civil_Rights_Movement\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Civil Rights Movement\">Civil Rights Movement</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Heed_Their_Rising_Voices&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://kingencyclopedia.stanford.edu/encyclopedia/encyclopedia/enc_state_of_alabama_v_m_l_king_jr_1956_and_1960/\">\"State of Alabama v. M. L. King, Jr. (1956 and 1960)\"</a>. <i>The Martin Luther King, Jr. Research and Education Institute</i>. Stanford University<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2 April</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Martin+Luther+King%2C+Jr.+Research+and+Education+Institute&amp;rft.atitle=State+of+Alabama+v.+M.+L.+King%2C+Jr.+%281956+and+1960%29&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fkingencyclopedia.stanford.edu%2Fencyclopedia%2Fencyclopedia%2Fenc_state_of_alabama_v_m_l_king_jr_1956_and_1960%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHeed+Their+Rising+Voices\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Hall-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Hall_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Hall_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Hall, Kermit L.; Patrick, John J. (2006). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=4upmi30oV8cC&amp;lpg=PA142&amp;dq=Heed%20Their%20Rising%20Voices&amp;pg=PA141#v=onepage&amp;q=Heed%20Their%20Rising%20Voices&amp;f=false\">\"Freedom of the Press in a Free Society\"</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=4upmi30oV8cC&amp;printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\"><i>The Pursuit of Justice: Supreme Court Decisions that Shaped America</i></a>. Oxford University Press. pp.&#160;141\u2013149. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780195311891\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780195311891\">9780195311891</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Freedom+of+the+Press+in+a+Free+Society&amp;rft.btitle=The+Pursuit+of+Justice%3A+Supreme+Court+Decisions+